      <section eId="sec_CC-3538">
        <num>CC 3538</num>
        <heading>3538. Â Form</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3538__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the law of the state of making;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3538__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the law of the state of performance to the extent that performance is to be rendered in that state;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3538__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the law of the state of common domicile or place of business of the parties; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3538__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the law governing the substance of the contract under Articles 3537 or 3540.
Nevertheless, when for reasons of public policy the law governing the substance of the contract under Article 3537 requires a certain form, there must be compliance with that form.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
